<h3 id="the-partially-surrendered-life">The Partially Surrendered Life</h3>

<ul>
  <li>I‚Äôll give God some <strong>things</strong>, but not <strong>everything</strong>.</li>
  <li>I don‚Äôt fully trust God with _____. (Fill in the blank.)</li>
  <li>I want God to prove Himself so I can trust Him.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="developing-a-wholehearted-trust">Developing a Wholehearted Trust</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Get to know the <strong>goodness</strong> of God.</li>
  <li>Get to know the <strong>love</strong> of God.</li>
  <li>Get to know the <strong>faithfulness</strong> of God.</li>
</ul>

<p>‚ÄúWe want God to prove Himself so we can trust Him. God wants us to trust Him so He can prove Himself.‚Äù</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="discussion-questions">Discussion Questions</h2>
<p class="lead">Start Talking: find a conversation starter for your group.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Name one thing that you‚Äôll never be able to fully control (but wish you could). Weather, spouse, time, age, boss, hair, cat?</li>
  <li>What‚Äôs one of the most controlling things you ever do with people? What‚Äôs one of the most trusting things you ever do?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start Thinking: ask questions to get your group thinking.</p>

<ul>
  <li>What are some practical, everyday actions you identify as showing trust in God?</li>
  <li>Put these items in order of how well you trust God with each: relationships, family, money, forgiveness, health, protection.</li>
  <li>What are some specific ways your life might look different if God had your complete trust?</li>
  <li>Who do you know that trusts God fully? What sets them apart?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start Sharing: choose questions that create openness.</p>

<ul>
  <li>I don‚Äôt fully trust God with <strong>__</strong>_. Fill in the blank with something, someone, or some specific way you aren‚Äôt trusting God.</li>
  <li>Tell a story of when you trusted God with something, and He came through in a way you didn‚Äôt expect.</li>
  <li>On a scale of 1 to 10‚Äîwhere 1 is knowing about God and 10 is knowing Him‚Äîwhere do you land today? Does this impact the way you trust Him?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start Praying: be bold and pray specifically.</p>

<ul>
  <li>God, thank You for Your goodness, faithfulness, and love. Help us move from knowing about You to knowing You, and from believing in You to trusting in You fully.</li>
</ul>

